{"kanda":6,"sarga":7,"description":"","verses":[{"v":1,"dev":"इत्युक्ताराक्षसेन्द्रेणराक्षसास्तेमहाबलाः ।ऊचुःप्रान्जलयःसर्वेरावणंराक्षसेश्वरम्","trans":"All the Rakshasas of mighty strength, having heard the Lord of Rakshasas, thus spoke to their leader, greeting with folded hands.","words":[{"d":"राक्षसेन्द्रेण:","m":"to the leader of Rakshasas"},{"d":"सर्वे:","m":"all Rakshasas"},{"d":"महाबलाः","m":"of mighty strength प्रान्जलयः greeting with folded hand s"},{"d":"राक्षसास्ते:","m":"the Rakshasas"},{"d":"राक्षसेश्वरम्:","m":"Lord of Rakshasas"},{"d":"रावणं:","m":"to Ravana ऊचुः having heard"},{"d":"इत्युक्ता:","m":"thus spoke."}]},{"v":2,"dev":"द्विषत्पक्षमविज्ञायनीतिबाह्यास्त्वबुद्धयः ।राजन्परिघशक्त्यृष्टिशूलपट्टिशकुन्तलम्","trans":"\"O King The ogres are not having political intelligence. They have submitted themselves, even though they are mighty and are having iron bars, javelins, sharp edged spears, and doubleedged swords.\"","words":[{"d":"राजन्:","m":"o king परिघ: iron bars"},{"d":"शक्त्यृष्टि:","m":"javelins"},{"d":"शूलपट्टि:","m":"arrows, and swords"},{"d":"शकुन्तलम्:","m":"sharp edged spears"},{"d":"द्विषत्पक्षम:","m":"double edged swords"},{"d":"अविज्ञाय:","m":"not  knowing"},{"d":"नीतिबाह्या:","m":"political intelligence"},{"d":"स्त्वबुद्धयः","m":"submitted by themselves."}]},{"v":3,"dev":"इत्युक्ताराक्षसेन्द्रेणराक्षसास्तेमहाबलाः ।ऊचुःप्रान्जलयःसर्वेरावणंराक्षसेश्वरम् द्विषत्पक्षमविज्ञायनीतिबाह्यास्त्वबुद्धयः ।","trans":"The Lord of Rakshasas having spoken like that, to the Rakshasas, who were very strong, but ignorant about the enemy's strength and who were not endowed with political wisdom, spoke to Ravana, the king of Rakshasas, the following words with folded hands.","words":[{"d":"इत्युक्ता:","m":"having spoken thus"},{"d":"राक्षसेन्द्रेण:","m":"by the Lord of Rakshasas"},{"d":"महाबलाः","m":"who were very strong"},{"d":"द्विषत्पक्षं:","m":"the enemy's side अविज्ञाय: ignorant about"},{"d":"नीतिबाह्या:","m":"without having political wisdom,  (नीतिबाह्यास्त्वबुद्धयःनीतिबाह्या:  तु  अबुद्धय:) अबुद्धय: not intelligent"},{"d":"ऊचुः","m":"told"},{"d":"प्रान्जलयः","m":"with folded hands"},{"d":"रावणं:","m":"to Ravana"},{"d":"राक्षसेश्वरम्:","m":"the king of Rakshasas."}]},{"v":4,"dev":"राजन्परिघशक्त्यृष्टिशूलपट्टिशकुन्तलम्","trans":"\"Oh king, (our army is equipped with) iron bars, javelins, double edged swords, spears, three pointed weapons, ploughs etc.\"","words":[{"d":"राजन्:","m":"Oh king"},{"d":"परिघ:","m":"iron bars"},{"d":"शक्ति:","m":"javelins"},{"d":"ऋष्टि:","m":"double edged swords"},{"d":"शूल:","m":"spear"},{"d":"पट्टिश:","m":"spear with a sharp edge or some other weapon with three points"},{"d":"कुन्तलम्:","m":"ploughs."}]},{"v":5,"dev":"सुमहन्नोबलंकस्माद्विषादंभजतेभवान् ।त्वयाभोगवतींगत्वानिर्जिताःपन्नगायुधि","trans":"\"Why are you despondent? You have huge and mighty army strength. When you went to Bhogavathi, the Nagas were subdued in war by your mighty army.\"","words":[{"d":"सुमहन्नोबलं:","m":"mighty army strength"},{"d":"कस्माद्:","m":"why"},{"d":"विषादं:","m":"despondent भजते: give way भवान्: you"},{"d":"त्वया:","m":"by you पन्नगा: Nagas"},{"d":"युधि:","m":"in war"},{"d":"भोगवतीं:","m":"Bhogavathi"},{"d":"गत्वा:","m":"going"},{"d":"निर्जिताः","m":"subdued"}]},{"v":6,"dev":"कैलासशिखरावासीयक्षैर्बहुभिरावृतः ।सुमहत्कदनंकृत्वावश्यस्तेधनदःकृतः","trans":"","words":[{"d":"कैलासशिखरावासी:","m":"he who lives on the peak of mount Kailas: बहुभि: numerous"},{"d":"यक्षै:","m":"Yakshas, (बहुभि:  आवृत:  बाहुभिरावृत:) आवृतः surrounded by"},{"d":"सुमहत:","m":"great"},{"d":"कदनं:","m":"sorrow कृत्वा: being caused"},{"d":"वश्यस्ते:","m":"surrendered to you"},{"d":"धनदः","m":"bestow er of wealth (Kubera) कृतः remained."}]},{"v":7,"dev":"समहेश्वरसख्येनश्लाघमानस्त्वयाविभो ।निर्जितःसमरेरोषाल्लोकपालोमहाबलः","trans":"\"O King Proud of his friendship with Lord Maheshwara (Siva), that mighty ruler of the world Kubera was subdued by you in the conflict.\"","words":[{"d":"स:","m":"that"},{"d":"महेश्वरसख्येन:","m":"by the friendship of Maheswara (Siva)"},{"d":"श्लाघमान:","m":"pridingमहाबलः strong"},{"d":"ल्लोकपालो:","m":"ruler of the world"},{"d":"स्त्वया:","m":"by you might"},{"d":"विभो:","m":"O king"},{"d":"निर्जितः","m":"subdued"},{"d":"समरे:","m":"in conflict."}]},{"v":8,"dev":"विनिहत्यचयक्षौघान्विक्षोभ्यचविनिगृह्यच ।त्वयाकैलासशिखराद्विमानमिदमाहृतम्","trans":"\"Causing terrific disturbance to the hordes of Yakshas and taking them as prisoners, you have brought the great aerial chariot from mount Kailas.\"","words":[{"d":"त्वया:","m":"by you"},{"d":"यक्षौघान्:","m":"hordes of yaksha"},{"d":"विनिहत्य:","m":"taking as prisoners"},{"d":"विक्षोभ्यच:","m":"causing disturbance by stirring and"},{"d":"विनिगृह्यच:","m":"and taking away"},{"d":"कैलासशिखराद्:","m":"from mount Kailas"},{"d":"विमानमिदमाहृतम्:","m":"brought this great aerial chariot."}]},{"v":9,"dev":"मयेनदानवेन्द्रेणत्वद्भयात्सख्यमिच्छता ।दुहितातवभार्यार्थेदत्ताराक्षसपुङ्गव","trans":"\"Maya, the ruler of Danavas has given his daughter (Mandodari) to you as a wife out of fear of you, O leader of Rakshasas\"","words":[{"d":"राक्षसपुङ्गव:","m":"leader of Rakshasas"},{"d":"दानवेन्द्रेण:","m":"ruler of Danavas"},{"d":"मयेन:","m":"by Maya"},{"d":"त्वद्भयात्:","m":"out of fear of you"},{"d":"मिच्छता:","m":"sought"},{"d":"सख्य:","m":"alliance"},{"d":"दत्ता:","m":"given तव: to you"},{"d":"भार्यार्थे:","m":"wife"},{"d":"दुहिता:","m":"daughter."}]},{"v":10,"dev":"दानवेन्द्रोमधुर्नामवीर्योत्सिक्तोदुरासदः ।विगृह्यवशमानीतःकुम्भीनस्याःसुखावहः","trans":"\"Madhu, another ruler of Danavas who was proud of his valour and difficult to approach, the husband of Kumbhinasi was subjugated by you by your offering to fight with him.\"","words":[{"d":"दुरासदः","m":"difficult to approach"},{"d":"वीर्योत्सिक्तो:","m":"proud of his valour"},{"d":"कुम्भीनस्याः","m":"Kumbhinasi (your sister)"},{"d":"सुखावहः","m":"who brings joy to her (who is husband of)"},{"d":"दानवेन्द्रो:","m":"ruler of Danavas"},{"d":"मधुर्नाम:","m":"called as Madhu"},{"d":"विगृह्य:","m":"offering to fight and win"},{"d":"वशमानीतः","m":"subjugated to you."}]},{"v":11,"dev":"निर्जितास्तेमहाबाहोनागागत्वारसातलम् ।वासुकिस्तक्षकःशङखोजटीचवशमाहृताः","trans":"\"O mighty armed king Going to the subterranean world, you won over the serpent demons Vasuki, Takshaka, Shanka and Jati and made them submit to you.\"","words":[{"d":"महाबाहो:","m":"mighty armed"},{"d":"स्ते:","m":"you गत्वा: going to"},{"d":"रसातलम्:","m":"subterranean region वासुकि:: Vasuki"},{"d":"तक्षकः","m":"Takshaka"},{"d":"शङखो:","m":"Shanka"},{"d":"जटीच:","m":"and Jati"},{"d":"नागा:","m":"serpent demons"},{"d":"र्जिता:","m":"winning over"},{"d":"वशमाहृताः","m":"made them submit to you."}]},{"v":12,"dev":"अक्षयाबलवन्तश्चशूरालब्धवराःपुनः ।त्वयासंवत्सरंयुद्ध्वासमरेदानवाविभो","trans":"\"The mighty and strong Danava warriors who had obtained boon were made to fight a war by you for one year.\"","words":[{"d":"अक्षया:","m":"imperishable"},{"d":"बलवन्तश्च:","m":"strong and mighty"},{"d":"शूरा:","m":"warriors"},{"d":"लब्धवराः","m":"who had obtained boon"},{"d":"त्वया:","m":"by you"},{"d":"संवत्सरं:","m":"one year"},{"d":"युद्ध्वा:","m":"fighting"},{"d":"पुनः","m":"again"},{"d":"समरे:","m":"in war"},{"d":"दानवा:","m":"Danavas"},{"d":"विभो:","m":"Oh Lord."}]},{"v":13,"dev":"स्वबलंसमुपाश्रित्यनीतावशमरिन्दम ।मायाश्चाधिगतास्तत्रबह्व्योवैराक्षसाधिप","trans":"\"O king of Rakshasas (Those Danavas) were reduced to sub mission by resorting to your own strength. Oh subduer of enemies, many deceitful tricks were learned from them.\"","words":[{"d":"राक्षसाधिप:","m":"king of Rakshasas"},{"d":"स्वबलं:","m":"your own strength"},{"d":"समुपाश्रित्य:","m":"resorting to"},{"d":"मायाश्च:","m":"deceitful tricks"},{"d":"अधिगता:","m":"learned"},{"d":"तत्र:","m":"there"},{"d":"बह्वो:","m":"many"},{"d":"नीता:","m":"reduced to"},{"d":"वशम:","m":"sub mission"},{"d":"अरिन्दम:","m":"subduer of enemies."}]},{"v":14,"dev":"शूराश्चबलवन्तश्चवरुणस्यसुतारणे ।निर्जितास्तेमहाभागचतुर्विधबलानुगाः","trans":"\"O blessed king Mighty strong sons of Varuna, heroes capable of war and of all the four kinds of army have been won by you.\"","words":[{"d":"महाभाग:","m":"blessed one"},{"d":"चतुर्विधबलानुगाः","m":"four kinds of army"},{"d":"शूराश्च:","m":"capable heroes"},{"d":"बलवन्तश्च:","m":"mighty strong"},{"d":"वरुणस्य:","m":"Varuna's"},{"d":"सुता:","m":"sons"},{"d":"रणे:","m":"in war"},{"d":"निर्जिता:","m":"have won"},{"d":"ते:","m":"by you."}]},{"v":15,"dev":"मृत्युदण्डमहाग्राहंशाल्मलिद्रुममण्डितम् ।कालपाशमहावीचिंयमकिंकरपन्नगम् महाज्वरेणदुर्धर्षंयमलोकमहार्णवम् ।अवगाह्यत्वयाराजन्यमस्यबलसागरम् जयश्चविपुलःप्राप्तोमृत्युश्चप्रतिषेधितः ।सुयुद्धेनचतेसर्वेलोकास्तत्रसुतोषिताः","trans":"\"Oh King Plunging into the ocean, which was in the shape of Yama's realm, with an enormous alligator in the form of rod of death, adorned with Salmali trees, turbulent with a huge wave in the form of Death 's noose, infested with Lord of Death's attendants as serpents, unassailable on account of the mighty Jwara (spirit of fever), you have obtained a great victory over the Lord of Death 's great army and the army was warded off. By your good battle all the people (of the world) were delighted.","words":[{"d":"मृत्युदण्ड:","m":"Yama's rod of death"},{"d":"महाग्राहं:","m":"huge alligator"},{"d":"शाल्मलिद्रुममण्डितम्:","m":"adorned with Salmali trees (bristling with thorns to be used as weapons)"},{"d":"कालपाश:","m":"noose of time (Kala)"},{"d":"महावीचिं:","m":"hugely turbulent wave"},{"d":"यमकिंकरपन्नगम्:","m":"Lord of death 's attendants as serpents"},{"d":"महाज्वरेण:","m":"on account of mighty Jwara (spirit of fever)"},{"d":"दुर्धर्षं:","m":"unassailable"},{"d":"यमलोकमहार्णवम्:","m":"ocean in the shape of Yama's realm"},{"d":"अवगाह्य:","m":"plunging into. त्वया: by you"},{"d":"राजन्:","m":"Oh King"},{"d":"यमस्य:","m":"realm of death"},{"d":"बलसागरम्:","m":"ocean of army"},{"d":"जयश्च:","m":"victory"},{"d":"विपुल:","m":"great"},{"d":"प्राप्तो:","m":"obtained"},{"d":"मृत्युश्च:","m":"and death"},{"d":"प्रतिषेधितः","m":"warded off"},{